Anuradha Lohia (n√©e Fatehpuria) is an Indian molecular parasitologist who works in infectious disease.  She is currently the Vice Chancellor of the Presidency University. She was earlier the Chairperson of Department of Biochemistry in the Bose Institute in Kolkata. She was Chairperson of an Indo-British Wellcome Trust/ DBT India Alliance, an organization to promote medical research in India.
